              },
              {
                "id": "57239c8c-7b30-41d0-baf6-0b455f298544",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.752263Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: When her daughter was three months old, Priya discovered through a WhatsApp group of new mothers that the infant formula brand she had been using was linked to a contamination complaint in Pune; she spent an entire weekend cross-referencing lab reports, FSSAI notices, and pediatrician opinions before switching brands. \u2014 This experience cemented her distrust of brand marketing and her reliance on peer networks for product validation, and it hardened her non-negotiable stance on quality over price for anything entering her household.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.752263Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "8ddebfd4-2bb9-453c-8c1a-6c85fb72e561",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.752894Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: While managing a product analytics rollout at her firm, Priya delegated a critical data validation module to a vendor who delivered flawed outputs three days before the client presentation, forcing her to rebuild the entire dataset overnight. \u2014 She internalized a deep resistance to relinquishing control over high-stakes tasks, creating a persistent tension between her capacity to scale her work and her compulsive need to personally verify every critical output.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.752894Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "1be5dd35-64dc-4236-8c7f-e6d9b60860fc",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.754615Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: Declining a coaching institute her colleagues swore by, Priya built a six-month self-directed study schedule using only official materials and scored in the 94th percentile, earning admission to a top Mumbai MBA program. \u2014 The success reinforced her analytical self-reliance and low social orientation \u2014 she learned to trust structured personal research over group consensus, a heuristic she now applies to financial, health, and parenting decisions alike.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.754615Z"
              }
