            "title": "The Defective Machinery Lesson",
            "when": "age 29",
            "event": "Mahesh purchased a batch of cheap Chinese-made cutting machines for his small garment workshop in Jaipur's Johari Bazaar area, saving nearly \u20b940,000 upfront, only to watch them break down within eight months and lose two major wholesale contracts due to inconsistent output quality.",
            "lasting_impact": "This experience hardwired his belief that cutting corners on quality always costs more in the long run, making him a methodical researcher who prioritizes durability and reliability over price \u2014 the core of his quality_vs_budget tension."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Partnership That Collapsed",
            "when": "age 35",
            "event": "Mahesh entered a business expansion partnership with a childhood friend to open a second workshop outlet, but the friend mismanaged funds and exited abruptly after fourteen months, leaving Mahesh to absorb losses of nearly \u20b91.8 lakh and deal with vendor disputes alone.",
            "lasting_impact": "The betrayal by someone he trusted deeply pushed his trust orientation firmly inward \u2014 he now relies almost exclusively on his own judgment and research before any significant financial or business decision, keeping his social orientation and external reliance very low."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Family Health Scare That Didn't Change Habits",
            "when": "age 44",
            "event": "After his wife Sunita was briefly hospitalized with gastric issues, a well-meaning neighbor pushed the family toward a strict keto and gluten-free regimen, but thorough consultation with a Jaipur-based gastroenterologist confirmed no clinical basis for these restrictions in their case.",
            "lasting_impact": "Mahesh's analytical nature led him to reject dietary fads unsupported by medical evidence, cementing his extremely low adherence to keto or gluten-sensitivity beliefs \u2014 he trusts verified data over popular wellness trends."
          }
