                "age_when": 27,
                "event": "When searching for their first flat in Hyderabad after marriage, he spent three weekends meticulously visiting 14 properties, building spreadsheets comparing sq footage, builder reputation, and resale value, ultimately choosing a slightly smaller flat in a reputed complex over a cheaper but poorly constructed option.",
                "lasting_impact": "Cemented his conviction that quality always justifies the price premium, creating the persistent quality-vs-budget tension he navigates in every significant purchase since."
              },
              {
                "age_when": 24,
                "event": "During his first job in Pune, he invested a modest \u20b940,000 in a sector-specific mid-cap fund on a colleague's tip, watched it drop 38% over eight months, and quietly redeemed it at a loss before his wedding savings could be affected.",
                "lasting_impact": "Hardwired a conservative financial disposition \u2014 he now keeps investments in fixed deposits and index funds, and his risk tolerance has never recovered above cautious."
