              {
                "id": "052e1d4f-f407-4bcb-85c4-e6b37a0fa269",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.561210Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: While completing her postgraduate degree, Priya watched her father lose a significant portion of his savings in a small-cap mutual fund that a neighbour had enthusiastically recommended, forcing him into a delayed retirement. \u2014 Witnessing this made her deeply skeptical of social financial advice and pushed her risk tolerance to a conservative floor, reinforcing her practice of trusting only family consensus on major decisions.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.561210Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "a82465c5-ed4d-425f-b275-1999e9a2e63d",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T06:59:24.561234Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: Her son Aarav was born two weeks premature and spent seven days in the NICU at a private Pune hospital, during which Priya single-handedly managed insurance paperwork, doctor consultations, and household logistics while her husband worked remotely. \u2014 The experience sharpened her analytical and planning instincts around family health and finances, making building a stable, well-resourced family unit her dominant life priority over social or career ambitions.",
